g.text: Shows the three main layers (Kernel eBPF, User-space Manager, Terminal Dashboard) and the data flow between them via BPF maps and ring buffers.

g.title: Attaches to kernel function entry/exit points
Attaches to stable kernel tracepoints
High-performance circular buffer for event streaming
Key-value store for aggregation and state tracking
Pre-binned histogram storage for latency metrics
Loads eBPF bytecode and attaches to kernel hooks
Polls perf ring buffer for new events
Aggregates and processes events from multiple sources
Reads/writes BPF maps from user space
Live scrolling view of system events
Visual representation of latency distribution
Shows active TCP connections and statistics
Interactive controls for filtering and pausing
